🎤 SIERA — 4-Minute Town Hall Script
~100 words per slide · ~130 words/min speaking pace

SLIDE 1 — Title (~30 sec)

"Thank you all for being here. Today I want to share something the team has built that's already changing how we handle sanctions screening. It's called SIERA — Sanctions Intelligence Engine for Risk Assessment. It uses AI to analyse payment alerts automatically, so our analysts spend time on real threats — not false alarms. Let me show you how."


SLIDE 2 — What is SIERA? (~60 sec)

"Every payment we process gets screened against a sanctions list. When there's a potential match — a hit — someone has to review it. The problem? Most hits are false positives. Names that look similar, not actual violations. Analysts were manually reviewing thousands of these every day.
SIERA fixes that. It's an AI layer that reads the full payment message, understands the context, and makes an intelligent recommendation — automatically. It supports both SWIFT and Fircosoft formats and feeds a live analytics dashboard so we can measure every decision it makes."


SLIDE 3 — AI Architecture (~60 sec)

"Here's how it works. A payment comes in through MQ, gets validated, and enters our AI pipeline.
Two agents work in sequence. The Primary Agent analyses the hit — checking entity name, type, country, context. Then the Critic Agent challenges that decision — confirming it's not just a name similarity.
Before any of that, the FME Rule Engine catches known false positive patterns and auto-releases them instantly — no AI needed, no analyst time wasted.
The result flows to Disposition — a clear, actionable recommendation."


SLIDE 4 — How It Works (~45 sec)

"Each alert goes through four steps: parse the message, enrich it with risk context — fields like Ordering Customer and Remittance carry higher risk — batch the hits for parallel processing, then compute and persist the final disposition.
We handle three message levels: Level 1 is new AI analysis, Level 2 escalates to a human analyst, and Level 3 feeds analyst decisions back into the system — so SIERA gets smarter over time."


SLIDE 5 — Metrics (~45 sec)

"And here are the real numbers.
12,456 alerts processed. 8,234 handled by AI — that's 66% autonomously.
Of those, 7,891 were auto-released as false positives. A 95.8% release rate.
Only 343 alerts — 4.2% — needed a human analyst. Those are the ones that actually matter.
That's the value. Thousands of hours of analyst time redirected toward genuine risk, not noise.
SIERA is live, it's working, and the team continues to improve it. Thank you."


